EBANX's Privacy Notice
March 7, 2024
This is EBANX's Privacy Notice, available at
https://www.ebanx.com
, where you can access information about all our services. EBANX takes your privacy very seriously and is committed to protecting your Personal Data throughout browsing and using our services.
This Notice explains how EBANX collects, uses, and shares your Personal Data. It also tells you how to access, update, and correct your Personal Data and exercise control over your information.
Glossary
Applicable Law:
any legislation or regulation that addresses privacy and data protection matters, according to the jurisdiction where EBANX operates.
Controller:
a natural or legal person governed by public or private law who is responsible for decisions regarding processing Personal Data.
Personal Data:
any information about an identified or identifiable natural person.
EBANX:
all the companies that are part of EBANX's economic group.
Merchant:
platforms or sites, national or international, that use EBANX as the means of processing payments.
Platform:
the website
https://www.ebanx.com
and the EBANX API.
Processor:
a natural or legal person, governed by public or private law, who processes Personal Data on behalf of the controller.
Processing:
is any operation carried out with Personal Data, such as those relating to the collection, production, reception, classification, use, access, reproduction, transmission, sharing, distribution, processing, archiving, storage, elimination, evaluation, or control of the information, modification, communication, transfer, dissemination or extraction.
Third Parties:
natural or legal persons who supply products or provide services to EBANX, whether public or private.
You:
any natural person who uses our services.
